column1: Gaming Revenue Granted to, and Earned by Community Organizations - 2012/13 Full Report (by community)
*  Multiculturalism grants were a one-time grant available in government fiscal year 2012/13 offered and funded by the Ministry of Finance and Minister Responsible for Multiculturalism.
Multiculturalism grants are not considered gaming grants, but are shown in this report because they were administered by the Gaming Policy and Enforcement Branch.
? Gaming event licence reported earnings as of June 19, 2013, including losses. It is estimated that total licensed gaming earnings in 2012/13 were approximately $35.2 million.
? This report does not include, or show, unused grant funds returned by an organization.
